I have lived here long enough and, traveled the country - outside of 'cities' - long enough to realize that things could always be worse. In many cases a LOT worse! What happens is that most reviews are written to by people who want the 'experience' but want/expect Pittsburgh style accommodations. It ain't gonna' happen in Vietnam and, it ain't gonna' happen in a Vietnamese owned/managed $15 a night hotel. Get over it Fluffy. They do need to service the A/C units, mine was operating at about 50% efficiency. Something else they just don't do. I was greeted well and they had actually put my name down for a room - I called first. The room was clean, the bed linen was nice and they had 'western' sized towels in the room. Wi-Fi worked well, there was abundant hot water. There were a few things broken but - this is Vietnam - they aren't real big on fixing things. They were not things of huge importance. They only serve breakfast in the restaurant and it's sparse. There are a lot of places, within walking distance, for breakfast and other meals. The only negative thing is that the clientele is 90% Vietnamese. They have no respect for anything or anyone. The slamming of doors, loud (screaming) conversations begin at about 5 AM - along with screaming yelling brats running the hallways. This continues until about 11 PM, if you're lucky. In my case the people upstairs had a fetish for re-arranging the furniture in the room...this began one morning at 3 AM. As opposed to some other reviewers...I found that some of the staff do speak limited English. Enough to help a little. They can all read and write it, try writing a note next time and you can always 'Mime' some other things! Not only do they love it when people do that but - it can be a big help. I will stay again and will put this down as a decent hotel. A cut above others in this price range.", 'NhÃ¬n chung phÃ²ng sáº¡ch sáº½ , thÃ¡i Ä‘á»™ phá»¥c vá»¥ tá»‘t .

Whenever I go to Danang for business or a short beach vacation, I always stay at this hotel (away from massive and pricey luxury hotels). The beach is just a 10 to 15 minute walk. This hotel location is near the 5 star resorts and restaurants. The owner is very friendly and is accommodating to my needs. They will serve you breakfast and do your laundry for a small fee. They will also help you get a motorbike rental. What I like: ** very close to fancy hotels and eateries (with budget restaurants nearby) ** clean rooms (you can ask them fresh bedsheets on check-in if you want) ** walkable distance to the beach and bars with live music ** the view is good, you can see the beach, trees, hotels... ** the staff are friendly (esp. the owner -- very sweet lady!) Just scraping the bottom of the barrel: ** WIFI is a bit slow (just go out the lobby or your room or go to the common balcony)', 'Clean, quiet and simple
I stayed here during the Tet holiday in January and there was not a lot of places open in Da Nang. You can walk to the beach or rent a scooter from the owner by the day. They provide a nice breakfast and a very accomodating. Also, they will do your laundry, which is great if you have been travelling by train and bus. There are 2 big resort hotels across the street that have really nice restaurants and beach facilties as well as an ATM. There are a few restaurants and cafes within walking distance of the hotel but not much else in this area.', 'Great for a short visit
We stayed only for two nights in this hotel and purely as a base so we could have a few days on the beach. The room wasnÂ´t huge but the bed was and the AC and fan excellent. TV not great but who wants to watch lots of TV on holiday. One thing though, our bedsheets werenÂ´t the cleanest, so make sure yours are. Wifi was ok once connected but may take a couple of tries to connect. Breakfast was personally great as we were the only people in the whole small hotel and so the lady could leisurely make us our eggs etc. The daughter of the woman was a sweetie and serving us our food. The guy on reception was nice but not overly enthusiastic but nothing to complain about. The hotel is about 15 minute walk from the beach, past all the ridiculous gigantic village resorts on the beachside of the road, and although you are absolutely dripping by the time you get there, the beautiful crystal clear sea awaits! No problem with this walk, IÂ´ve seen other reviews moaning about it, donÂ´t know why. ItÂ´s flat, on a path, and passes lots of shops and bars so plenty of opportunities to stop if necessary. Price is fantastic so really canÂ´t complain too much. Overall was fine to stay for a couple of nights to wash off the sand.', 'welcomed like home']
